==English==

===Etymology===
From {{F.}}, ''[[répondez|Répondez]] [[s'il vous plaît]]'' (Reply if you please)
==== Initialism ====
'''rsvp'''
# (''at the end of a letter'') Please reply

==== Verb ====
'''rsvp'''

# ''(informal'') To respond to an invitation, usually to indicate that one will be coming to the corresponding event.
#* ''Have you '''rsvped''' for the party yet?''
#* ''I only just '''rsvped''' to the wedding invitation last Wednesday.''

===== Usage note =====
Generally one rsvps ''to'' invitations and rsvps ''for'' events, as in the example sentences provided.


